      "type": "add",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "462476fe-cb11-43c6-b630-c06471759ea7",
        "text": "Open Journal Systems (OJS) was designed to facilitate the development of open access ([[Open access (publishing)]]), [[peer-reviewed]] publishing, providing the technical infrastructure not only for the online presentation of journal articles, but also an entire editorial management workflow, including: article submission, multiple rounds of peer-review, and indexing. OJS relies upon individuals fulfilling different roles, such as the Journal manager, editor, reviewer, author, reader, etc. It has a module that supports subscription journals.[http://www.qualitative-research.net/index.php/fqs/help/view/journal/topic/000025 Subscriptions][http://pkp.sfu.ca/?q=ojs Open Journal Systems] - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_Journal_Systems#Design wikipedia]"
      },
      "after": "d84d58ba-910e-44cf-addc-069ba44910b7",
      "id": "462476fe-cb11-43c6-b630-c06471759ea7",
      "date": 1535195288780
    },
    {
      "type": "add",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "fa583ecf-f19c-4251-80f3-e834974e8dc0",
        "text": "The software has a 'plugin' architecture, similar to other community-based projects such as [[WordPress]], allowing new features to be easily integrated  without the need to change the entire core code base. Some of the plugins contributed to OJS include tools to facilitate indexing in [[Google Scholar]] and [[PubMed Central]], a feed plugin providing RSS ([[RSS (file format)]])/Atom ([[Atom (standard)]]) web syndication feeds, a COUNTER plugin,[http://www.projectcounter.org/about.html COUNTER (Counting Online Usage of Networked Electronic Resources]  allowing COUNTER ([[Project COUNTER]]) statistics and reporting, and more. OJS is also [[LOCKSS]]-compliant, helping to ensure permanent archiving for ongoing access to the content of the journal."
      },
      "after": "462476fe-cb11-43c6-b630-c06471759ea7",
